node.text: I was only seven years old when I saw it for the first time. I have no idea how many hundreds of times I have seen this movie since, or how many times I made my kids watch it over the years, but I often watch it when I’m feeling like I need to be cheered up or I need to feel warm and fuzzy and safe. It makes me really happy and I love all the lessons it teaches along the way. It’s probably why I grew up wanting to have a really big family. I’m so sad to hear today of the passing of Christopher Plummer… One of the things he often said was what a wonderful life he’s had. My love thoughts and prayers go out to his family and my gratitude and appreciation for all the wonderful roles he played and how he always made me feel when I watched the sound of music... God rest his soul 🙏❤️

node.title: The sound of music is my favorite movie.

node.text: Happy Birthday to my gorgeous and beautiful (inside and out) girlfriend of over 46 years!!!!! @jmkraines I can hardly believe how fast time rolls by and I will always be so grateful for all of the most magical and wonderful memories we have made along the way!!! Thank you for your friendship, for helping me raise my kids, and for being there for me while I was growing up!!!!! You are such an amazing friend, wife, mommy, grandmother, and auntie, and I am completely blessed to have you in my life to grow old with! I love you Joycie and wish you a day filled with so much love and joy!! Xo🥳🥰🙏😍🎂💋😍
